race.description: Tabtouch - Have You Got The Touch Hcp (C1)
race.comment: SHAZAIR (5) showed promise in her debut campaign when tackling the Natasha Stakes before a spell. Her latest trial was very good and suggested she's ready to fire on resumption for Fiore. 1400m is ideal and with this race lacking depth, she can resume on a winning note. RIVERCREST MAGIC (11) hasn't been far away in her past couple of events. This is tougher than what she faced last time out, but her run two back in this grade suggests she can make her presence felt. Can feature down in the weights. PURE OBSESSION (2) was very good on return at Northam, ending up 1.8L off the winner, but he laid the foundations for a strong campaign. Can improve on that performance now and looks capable of going to the next level. OLAF THE SNOWMAN (8) can also improve out in trip and with the blinkers on for the first time. FLINDERS LANE (9) is better than she showed first-up and bounce back to form.
